Third Shot - After getting ready, going out with someone else, prepared for the cold, with a warm jacket to go for a walk.

 Fifth plan - Take those Rare Beauty cosmetic products from the case and others and put them on the top of the dresser, organized so that you can use them all to put on makeup and smell nice.

caption:
Para celebrar el Mes de la Herencia Latine, invitamos amiges a devolver flores a quienes los ayudaron florecer. 
 
Inspirado por las sabias palabras de nuestra querida Judith Serrato, Retail Operations Coordinator (she/her) @judithserrato13, el #RareConsejo de este año, “Una flor no florece sola,” nos recuerda la importancia de no solo aplaudir los sacrificios que hacemos para ayudar a otros a crecer, sino también la importancia de nutrirnos a nosotros mismos. Cuando una comunidad se anima unos a otros, todos tenemos la oportunidad de florecer. 
 
Comparten sus #RareConsejos de Septiembre y devuelve flores a quienes te han ayudado florecer. 
 
💐💐💐💐💐💐💐💐💐 

To celebrate Latine Heritage Month, we invited friends to give flowers back to those who helped them bloom. 
 
Inspired by the wise words of our very own Judith Serrato, Retail Operations Coordinator (she/her) @judithserrato13, this year’s #RareConsejos, “Una flor no florece sola,” reminds us to embrace not only the sacrifices we make to help others grow, but also the importance of nurturing ourselves. When a community lifts one another, we all have the chance to blossom. 
 
Share your September #RareConsejos story and give flowers back to those who’ve helped you bloom.

caption:
Nos unimos con @kidsofimmigrants para celebrar la belleza de nuestro #RareConsejo de este año, “Una flor no florece sola”, creamos esta bolsa como símbol de la belleza y la audacia de dos marcas Latines basados en Los Ángeles.  
 
El diseño está inspirado de las experiencias, crecimiento, y la belleza de una comunidad que se nutre unos a otros, permitiéndonos florecer juntos.
Para compartir este momento especial con nuestra comunidad Latine, regalaremos dos pares de estas bolsas exclusivos de @kidsofimmigrants x @rarebeauty 
 
Para participar:
- Dale “Me Gusta” a esta publicación
- Regalate tus flores a ti misme y a una persona especial en tu vida en los comentarios 💐 
 
El sorteo se acabará el 21 de Septiembre a las 12pm PT. Dos ganadores serán elegidos, y recibirán un mensaje directo por medio de Rare Beauty.

@Lasfotosproject capturó el amor y el aprecio entre nuestra comunidad regalando flores a los que sacrificaron tanto para que nosotros podamos prosperar. Comparte tus #RareConsejos de Septiembre y regálale flores a quienes te han ayudado florecer en los comentarios.
 
Mucho amor a las fotógrafas Mia Rovira @unicasemmia y Michelle Montenegro @dr3amingofu por capturar estos momentos.

💐💐💐💐💐💐💐

@Lasfotosproject captured the love and appreciation as our community gave flowers to those who sacrificed so much so they could flourish. Share your September #RareConsejos and give flowers back to those who’ve helped you bloom in the comments.
 
Big love to photographers Mia Rovira @unicasemmia and Michelle Montenegro @dr3amingofu for capturing these moments. 

📸 Fotógrafos: @lasfotosproject (@unicasemmia @dr3amingofu)

💄Maquillaje: @cynth_pop @erikaaapadillaaa @ydderfc

caption:
Today marks 4 years of Rare Beauty 🥹❤️

Together we’ve raised $15M+ for the Rare Impact Fund to help support youth mental health globally, touched down in 36 countries (!!! we got to meet so many of you IRL), and have created a safe space where everyone is celebrated for makes them unique.

This is all because of YOU. Thank you for your endless support and for believing in our mission. We’re just getting started.

caption:
Whether you’re dealing with stress, anxious to head back to school, or currently navigating grief, we understand that change can make the journey to self-acceptance feel even more challenging.

We tapped Rare Impact Fund mental health partner @mindfullife_project to create an affirmation word search that can help during this time. Share the first #rarereminder that catches your eye to claim it today.

—

The Rare Impact Fund was launched as part of our focus on addressing mental health. We’re committed to raising awareness and increasing access to mental health services for young people by supporting organizations that expand access to mental health services.

1% of all sales go to the Rare Impact Fund to support mental health for young people all over the world.

—

If you are in the United States and need suicide or mental health-related crisis support, or are worried about someone else, please call or text 988. Your call will be directed to a local mental health crisis center.

If you are located internationally, please visit findahelpline.com for a global list of helplines, hotlines, and crisis lines that can support you.

caption:
From Australia based Rare Impact Fund mental health partner @batyraus, swipe ➡️ for reminders on grief in honor of National Grief Awareness Day, August 30. 

Griefline Australia provides free and confidential counseling and support to people experiencing grief and loss. Call 1-300-84-5745 (6am – midnight AEST) to start a conversation today. 

If you’re in need of more immediate mental health support, please call Lifeline on 13-11-14 or Kids Helpline on 1-800-55-1800. 

—

If you are in the United States and need suicide or mental health-related crisis support, or are worried about someone else, please call or text 988. Your call will be directed to a local mental health crisis center.
 
If you are located internationally, please visit findahelpline.com for a global list of helplines, hotlines, and crisis lines that can support you.

—

The Rare Impact Fund was launched as part of Rare Beauty’s focus on addressing mental health. We’re committed to raising awareness and increasing access to mental health services for young people by supporting organizations that expand access to mental health services.
 
1% of all Rare Beauty sales go to the Rare Impact Fund to support mental health for young people all over the world.

Following our celebrations of AAPI Heritage Month and honoring PRIDE Month, we’re excited to spotlight our amazing Rare Impact Fund grantees who work within intersectional communities to help make mental health resources and education accessible.

—

The Rare Impact Fund was launched as part of Rare Beauty’s focus on addressing mental health. We’re committed to raising awareness and increasing access to mental health services for young people by supporting organizations that expand access to mental health services.

1% of all Rare Beauty sales go to the Rare Impact Fund to support mental health for young people all over the world.

—

If you are in the United States and need suicide or mental health-related crisis support, or are worried about someone else, please call or text 988. Your call will be directed to a local mental health crisis center.

If you are located internationally, please visit findahelpline.com for a global list of helplines, hotlines, and crisis lines that can support you.

caption:
Here’s your reminder to pick up the phone and call someone. 

When you’re feeling lonely, sometimes all it takes is one phone call to a loved one to boost your mood (and research shows this is true!). 

*A study called “”Instant messages vs. speech: hormones and why we still need to hear each other”” found that hearing a loved one’s voice lowers our stress hormone (cortisol) and increases our feel-good hormone (oxytocin). Researchers believes it’s not so much *what’s* being said, but hearing a comforting voice that makes a difference.

—

Call us at 877-HEY-RARE for a feel good boost.​

Need more than a familiar voice? For immediate support for yourself or someone else, call the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline 24/7 at 988. If you’re outside the U.S., please visit findahelpline.com for a global list of helplines, hotlines, and crisis lines that can support you.

alt: Photo by Rare Beauty by Selena Gomez on May 01, 2024.
caption:
Introducing 877-HEY-RARE — our feel-good phone line!​

Feeling lonely? You’re not alone. About a quarter of people worldwide feel the same way. Research suggests a comforting voice can boost our feel-good hormone.​

In honor of Mental Health Awareness Month, we invite you to pick up the phone. It’s always a good call.​

Who to dial:​
📞 Call someone you miss, or someone who’d love to hear your voice.​
📞 Call us! Try 877-HEY-RARE for a quick and easy mood boost.​
📞 Need more than a familiar voice? For immediate support for yourself or someone else, call the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline 24/7 at 988. If you’re outside the U.S., please visit findahelpline.com for a global list of helplines, hotlines, and crisis lines that can support you.

alt: Photo by Rare Beauty by Selena Gomez on May 01, 2024.
caption:
You (yes, you!) have all been huge help in fostering a safe, welcoming, and stigma-free space within our community, and today, we are so proud to share our 2023 Rare Beauty Social Impact Report.
 
With a focus on mental health and self-acceptance, Rare Impact aims to support our employees and global community through partnerships with mental health advocates and experts, creators, and non-profit grantees.
 
Visit the link in profile to learn more about the steps we have taken together to reduce the stigma associated with mental health and provide young people with access to the resources they need.
 
—
 
The Rare Impact Fund was launched by our Founder Selena Gomez as part of Rare Beauty’s commitment to addressing mental health and self-acceptance.
 
One percent of all Rare Beauty sales are donated to the Fund, to expand access to mental health services and education for young people around the world.

caption:
Call us at 877-HEY-RARE now. ​

We’re proud to share this phone line full of #rarereminder voice notes from our very own team to YOU. ​

Making the choice to call a loved one when you’re feeling lonely can often feel difficult. Whether you feel as if you have no one to call, or maybe you’re worried about feeling like a burden, we’re here for you. ​

You are not alone. ​

—

Need more than a familiar voice? For immediate support for yourself or someone else, call the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline 24/7 at 988. If you’re outside the U.S., please visit findahelpline.com for a global list of helplines, hotlines, and crisis lines that can support you.​

alt: Photo by Rare Beauty by Selena Gomez on April 30, 2024.
caption:
Whether it’s walking past a stranger with a smile or picking up the phone to call a loved one, creating a connection can change the course of someone’s day in a positive way. ​

About a quarter of people worldwide say they feel lonely (Gallup, 2023). From the beginning, founder @selenagomez’s mission for Rare Beauty has always been to create a safe, warm, and welcoming space so everyone in this community feels less alone. ​

You never know what others are going through. This is your #rarereminder to be kind, share a smile, or simply say “hello.”

— 

If you are in the United States and need suicide or mental health-related crisis support, or are worried about someone else, please call or text 988. Your call will be directed to a local mental health crisis center. 
 
If you are located internationally, please visit findahelpline.com for a global list of helplines, hotlines, and crisis lines that can support you.

caption:
How you react when you are stressed does not define you. 
 
Stress is normal and feeling the natural fight, flight or freeze response to triggers are different for everyone. From Rare Impact Fund Grantee, McLean Hospital, here are three things to consider adding to your day-to-day life to avoid, prevent, or manage stress: 
 
🚶 Movement – whether it’s a short walk or fitness class you’ve been wanting to try 
💞 Community – calling a loved one to vent or ask for help 
👭 Connection – meeting up with friends who fill your cup 
 
With today being National Stress Awareness Day, we encourage you to find the tiny moments of comfort in your day that help you feel at ease. 
 
— 

McLean Hospital is a leader in psychiatric care, research, and education and is a psychiatric affiliate of Harvard Medical School.
 
The Rare Impact Fund was launched as part of Rare Beauty’s focus on addressing mental health. We’re committed to raising awareness and increasing access to mental health services for young people by supporting organizations that expand access to mental health services. 
 
1% of all Rare Beauty sales go to the Rare Impact Fund to support mental health for young people all over the world.
 
— 
 
If you are in the United States and need suicide or mental health-related crisis support, or are worried about someone else, please call or text 988. Your call will be directed to a local mental health crisis center.

caption:
We’re proud to be founded on inclusivity, and today, we’re expanding our definition with the Made Accessible Initiative. 
 
Because of her personal experience, Selena has always been drawn to packaging that’s easy to open and close, hold, and apply. When we started hearing your feedback about how accessible *you* find our products, we wanted to know more. 
 
We partnered with the Casa Colina Research Institute (CCRI), part of Casa Colina Hospital and Centers for Healthcare, to identify features that make our products easy to open and close, hold, or apply for individuals with dexterity issues. Since then, seven products have aligned with our Made Accessible Initiative. And this is only the beginning! 
 
We’re so grateful to our community for pushing this conversation and inspiring this program. This is makeup made to feel good in—and to feel good using. 
 
About Casa Colina: 
 
Casa Colina Hospital and Centers for Healthcare is a nonprofit provider of specialized medical and rehabilitative care for people with disabling conditions resulting from accidents, disease, or illness. 
 
CCRI brings together doctors, scientists, and other rehabilitation professionals who conduct basic, translational, and clinical research, striving to transform scientific advances into improved patient care and outcomes. 
 
Learn more at rarebeauty.com/pages/made-accessible

Celebrating #BlackHistoryMonth doesn’t stop just because it’s the end of the month. We encourage you to continue amplifying and uplifting voices within the Black community, especially in mental health, all year long by following these resources ⬆️

Thank you to the amazing Rare Impact Fund Grantees and more for this directory of Black-led and Black-founded youth mental health resources.

—

The Rare Impact Fund was launched as part of Rare Beauty’s focus on addressing mental health. We’re committed to raising awareness and increasing access to mental health services for young people by supporting organizations that expand access to mental health services.

1% of all Rare Beauty sales go to the Rare Impact Fund to support mental health for young people all over the world.
